::Spears::

She could only see the ceiling and parts of the walls.  She could 
tell that something was wrong, but couldn't tell or see what it was.  
She yelled again,"HEEELLLPPPP! SOMEONE HELP!"  She wiggled under the 
straps and tried to move, but the straps were too tight.  She was 
starting to panic.  Then she stopped moving as she heard the walls 
around the lab groan and whine.  The lab wasmade of re-enforced 
beamed and usually the last thing to go in a ship.  Now she was part 
of a beam fall from the ceiling and watched it fall, missing her and 
the table by a few inches, then a loud crash as it hit the floor.
She screamed out again and hoped that someone would hear her.   
She tried to move her head up to cut throught the straps with her 
optic lazars, but her head was atrapped down to the table.  She 
started crying out of fear.  Being a warrior meant being brave in 
battle, but the warrior trainer's manual never mentioned anything 
about staying on a table, waiting to die.  She shook under the straps 
and yelled out again.  Then part of the wall started to come down.  
It fell on top of her,tipping the table over on it's side.  She was 
pinned between the table and a cabinet.  She was hit all over from 
falling debrie and metal as the room came down around her.  She was 
hit in the head by a large chunk of metal from the ceiling.  She was 
knocked out cold. Still strapped to the table, now on it's side.
